$WYNN Interactive earlier today announced that it and the SPAC Austerlitz mutually agreed to terminate their previously announced merger that would have taken Wynn Interactive (WynnBet) public. The termination is effective immediately, the companies said in a statement.

Not taking WynnBet public follows $WYNN 's plan to spend less on marketing and promos and focus more on ROI, Wynn Interactive CEO Craig Billings said in a statement. "We expect the capital intensity of the business to decline meaningfully beginning in the first quarter of 2022.
